main event: On September 18, 1957, a bright object was observed, emitting red light that later changed to green for a duration of 15 minutes. The conclusion was inconclusive, suggesting it could possibly be a balloon or aircraft, and insufficient for evaluation.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 15 minutes, allowing for a detailed view of the object.
The object emitted red light initially, then changed to green, indicating a change in its behavior or composition.
The report was inconclusive, suggesting the possibility of the object being a balloon or an aircraft, highlighting the challenge of identifying UFOs at the time.
The observation was made using binoculars, indicating a deliberate effort to enhance the view of the unidentified object.
The sighting location was Steelrock, Oregon, and the senior controller believed it to be Venus due to its movement in the sky.
sighted object: bright object emitting red light that changed to green
witnesses: Mrs._________, senior controller Chas W. Finnegan
